rComments: Professor Poon is super sweet and has a great sense of humour, but she often reads from the slides in lecture, which can be frustrating. Overall, her optimism and enthusiasm made the course more interesting, but it was still a fair amount of work required to succeed.

Joyce poon is most responsible prof here. She is very caring and always willing to help her students, also she is very very lovely and beautiful. The course is easy as a whole because it does not involve theoretical foundations like discrete lattice symmetry group and solid state physics, rather it focuses on practical things like device operations

Took course back in 2015. Everyone agreed that quizzes are overly hard, even more the project & final. Think reason was her 1st time teaching this course. Based on recent comments, the difficulty came down quite a bit. Even though she's a very lovely person, her courses are still quite hard in general (eg: optical networks)

ECE335 is not an easy course but very rewarding. Prof. Poon makes the lectures very interesting. She is very clear about what she expects you to know on a test and you have to do the homework and learn how to solve equations in order to do well. Prof. Poon is very approachable and answers lots of questions online. Great course!
She is just a slides-reader... The tests difficulty can not be imagined by only  solving problems she presents on classes...

She is probably the most responsible professor I have ever seen - she holds office hour and makes her own lectures slides, while there are some professors who never reply to their emails or come to the lectures unprepared. She makes fair exams and has a very clear and transparent grading criteria.
not clear, teaching without any logic.
Very clear and enthusiastic in teaching. The problem sets are tough, and the exam very tough, but its bell curved significantly so the course average is pretty good.
Very clear in class and notes are amazing.  Also very friendly and approachable.  The exam was ridiculously hard however...
